{"id": 1405, "title": "Ticket #1405: ConvertDefaultIPToSocketIP can break TCP_FORWARDING_HOST", "description": "<blockquote>\nPeter Doherty at Harvard found when using <code>glideinWMS</code> that when using TCP_FORWARDING_HOST on the the collector/schedd machine that the startds are trying to connect back to the schedd's CCB connection request on the schedd's private address rather than the address specified by TCP_FORWARDING_HOST.\n\n<p>The problem is caused by <code>ConvertDefaultIPToSocketIP()</code>.</p></blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2010-May-17 08:59</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/387c76e72dc69b2a521fa3c561b014484d461047\">[18015]</a></span>: Added ENABLE_ADDRESS_REWRITING to the param table. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=1405\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('1405'); return false;\" title=\"ConvertDefaultIPToSocketIP can break TCP_FORWARDING_HOST\">#1405</a></span>  (By Dan Bradley )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2010-May-14 15:24</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/2781d1d8b426b21072a6d356926589e27b3fd4d3\">[25490]</a></span>: Documented fix for TCP_FORWARDING_HOST. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=1405\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('1405'); return false;\" title=\"ConvertDefaultIPToSocketIP can break TCP_FORWARDING_HOST\">#1405</a></span>  (By Dan Bradley )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2010-May-13 16:27</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/07f5ac937aa856ba124ab9fb9757a40bc8cf5ba6\">[17989]</a></span>: Disable address rewriting when TCP_FORWARDING_HOST is defined. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=1405\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('1405'); return false;\" title=\"ConvertDefaultIPToSocketIP can break TCP_FORWARDING_HOST\">#1405</a></span> Also added ENABLE_ADDRESS_REWRITING so this feature can be turned off if it ever causes more trouble.  (By Dan Bradley )</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>", "type": "defect", "last_change": "2010-Jun-14 09:55", "status": "resolved", "created": "2010-May-13 16:12", "fixed_version": "2010-May-13 16:12", "broken_version": "v070400", "priority": "4", "subsystem": "", "assigned_to": "danb", "derived_from": "", "creator": "danb", "rust": "", "customer_group": "users", "visibility": "public", "notify": "", "due_date": "20100514"}